messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/articles/{slug}

All HTTP methods acceptable
- false

Methods accepted (based on explicit router registrations in the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- ArticleRetrieve is registered in ArticlesAnonymousRegister as router.GET("/:slug", ArticleRetrieve).
- ArticlesAnonymousRegister is called with v1.Group("/articles") in main (hello.go).
- v1 is defined as r.Group("/api") in main, so the route's full prefix is /api + /articles and the route path is /:slug â†’ /api/articles/:slug. Path parameters are presented above as {slug}.
- The code explicitly registers GET for "/:slug". PUT and DELETE for "/:slug" are also explicitly registered in ArticlesRegister (router.PUT("/:slug", ArticleUpdate) and router.DELETE("/:slug", ArticleDelete)), which is mounted at the same v1.Group("/articles") (after applying different auth middleware). Because we follow the code, PUT and DELETE are considered acceptable for the same full path.
- No explicit registrations for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PATCH, or POST at the exact path /:slug exist in the code, so those methods are reported as not acceptable (the POST routes present in the project target different paths like "/" or "/:slug/favorite" or "/:slug/comments", not "/:slug"). 
- "All methods" is false because the code does not register a catch-all (e.g., router.Any) for that path.
